Reports 'Comparator' instances defined as lambda expressions that could be expressed using 'Comparator.comparing()' calls. Chained comparisons which can be replaced by 'Comparator.thenComparing()' expression are also reported. Example: 'myList.sort((person1, person2) -> person1.getName().compareTo(person2.getName()));

  myList2.sort((person1, person2) -> {
      int res = person1.first().compareTo(person2.first());
      if(res == 0) res = person1.second().compareTo(person2.second());
      if(res == 0) res = person1.third() - person2.third();
