Reports arrays of enum constants that can be replaced with a call to 'EnumType.values()'. Usually, when updating such an enum, you have to update the array as well. However, if you use 'EnumType.values()' instead, no modifications are required. Example: 'enum States {
     NOT_RUN, IN_PROGRESS, FINISHED;
  }

  handleStates(new States[] {NOT_RUN, IN_PROGRESS, FINISHED});' After the quick-fix is applied: 'handleStates(States.values());' New in 2019.1

