Reports bitwise mask expressions which are guaranteed to evaluate to 'true' or 'false'. The inspection checks the expressions of the form '(var & constant1) == constant2' or '(var | constant1) == constant2', where 'constant1' and 'constant2' are incompatible bitmask constants. Example: '// Incompatible mask: as the mask ends in 00,
  // the result could be 0x1200 but not 0x1234
  if ((mask & 0xFF00) == 0x1234) {...}'

